  "body": "We have need to support multiple Availability Sets in an Azure cluster, but a load balancer can only target nodes that are in the same Availability Set.\n\nI suggest that we add another field to the configuration used by the Azure CloudProvider to indicate what Availability Set we want to include in the loadbalancer. Then, when we loop over the nodes in the cluster, we only add nodes in that Availability Set to the load balancer backend.\n\nCC: @anhowe @brendandburns \n",
